          <body>
              <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#IG" source="#autopsy">
                      <div type="textpart" subtype="lamina"> <!-- remove corresp attribute from textparts -->
                             <ab>
                                 <lb n="1" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/><expan><abbr>Caecilior</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> Serv   
                                 <lb n="2" style="text-direction:r-to-l" break="no"/>iliani et Potiti 
                                 <lb n="3" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>Herenniani <expan><abbr>iun</abbr><ex>ioris</ex></expan>
                             </ab>
                      </div>
                  </div>
              <div type="apparatus">
                  <listApp>
                      <app><note>Text from autopsy.</note></app>
                  </listApp>
              </div>
              <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#IG">
                  <p>of Caecilii Servilianus and Potitus (and?) Herennianus the younger.</p>
              </div>
              <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#IG">
                  <p>dei Caecilii Servilianus e Potitus (e?) Herennianus il giovane.</p>
              </div>
              <div type="commentary">
                  <p xml:lang="en">Family company, composed of two or three members, depending on whether one wants to recognise one - Potiti Herenniani iun(oris) - or two - Potiti (et) Herenniani iun(ioris) - distinct persons in the second part of the text.</p>
              </div>
